00:41:45.820 --> 00:41:48.280
I don't know how to do that.

00:41:48.280 --> 00:41:50.890
I've thought about it a lot.

00:41:50.890 --> 00:41:55.990
What I know how to do is make
my art and make my own choices.

00:41:55.990 --> 00:41:59.400
When I made my movie, I
said from the beginning,

00:41:59.400 --> 00:42:01.060
before we even
hired the writer, "I

00:42:01.060 --> 00:42:03.440
want to play a woman
married to a woman married

00:42:03.440 --> 00:42:04.840
to a woman of color."

00:42:04.840 --> 00:42:07.520
Because if I'm
making this movie,

00:42:07.520 --> 00:42:11.820
I want to create an extra
role for a diverse woman,

00:42:11.820 --> 00:42:18.600
a woman from the LGBT
community, and a woman.

00:42:18.600 --> 00:42:22.700
So I hit those three checks.

00:42:22.700 --> 00:42:28.470
Now, I did hire an actual
African-American woman.

00:42:28.470 --> 00:42:35.020
It's tricky, then, to
go, "oh, is it OK for me

00:42:35.020 --> 00:42:38.710
to ask people are you gay?"

00:42:38.710 --> 00:42:40.960
That's actually discrimination.

00:42:40.960 --> 00:42:42.770
when I am casting
